import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='time', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of GitHub activity over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='ignore')
    data_by_hour = data.groupby('hour')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    ax = sns.barplot(x='hour', y='count', data=data_by_hour)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of GitHub activity by hour of the day?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
